Let's hope that, after those flunks with THE SPIRIT and MACHETE KILLS, Frank Miller and Robert Rodriguez can reunite and bring SIN CITY back to the big screen the way they did a decade ago. text: Well, lets see: The first Sin City movie was AMAZING and loved by everyone, mainly what made it great was the fact that Robert Rodriguez actually STUCK to the graphic novel by Frank Miller and even brought Miller in to Direct, instead of taking something precious and butchering it (as Hollywood loves to do) Also R.Rodriguez brought in one of his best friends to help direct; Quentin Tarantino, All of this made the film FANTASTIC. Now, from what we can see, R.R. brought Frank Miller in to Direct AGAIN, also, Robert Rodriguez has NEVER disappointed. So im gonna go "out on a limb" here and say Yes, this film is going to be "good". ITS GOING TO BE GREAT!
